      "level": 1,
      "text": "OPERATION"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "In \"Ds\" position, the plunger allows the circuit to drain, the engine brake valve spool is overcome by spring pressure and moves to the left. The engine brake valve arm, therefore, moves the shift control valve to the left, regardless of the position of the shift cam.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
